:R-HSA-8939211  a           obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "Estrogens are a class of hormones that play a role in physiological processes such as development, reproduction, metabolism of liver, fat and bone, and neuronal and cardiovascular function (reviewed in Arnal et al, 2017; Haldosen et al, 2014). Estrogens bind estrogen receptors, members of the nuclear receptor superfamily. Ligand-bound estrogen receptors act as nuclear transcription factors to regulate expression of genes that control cellular proliferation and differentiation, among other processes, but also play a non-genomic role in rapid signaling from the plasma membrane (reviewed in Hah et al, 2014;Schwartz et al, 2016)." ;
        rdfs:label          "ESR-mediated signaling" ;
        dc:contributor      "Reviewed: Magnani, Luca, 2018-02-23" , "Authored: Rothfels, Karen, 2017-09-29" , "Edited: Rothfels, Karen, 2017-11-03" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
